<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FF18FCF4FECB" blockId="12.[178,1085,219,358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
Head (
<figureCitation id="1347A39AFFB5F97892D6FF18FEADFF5F" box="[246,319,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 28-37" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1446,1466]" captionTargetBox="[188,1082,208,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[178,1085,208,1418]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 28-37: Bellatheta diacangica nov.sp. (28-32), Tropimenelytron sinuosum nov.sp. (33-35), and Oroekklina excaecata (ASSING) (36-37): (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30-31) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (32) spermatheca; (33) male tergites VI-VII; (34) female tergite VIII; (35) female sternite VIII; (36) male tergite VIII; (37) male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 28: 1.0 mm; 29, 33: 0.5 mm; 34-37: 0.2 mm; 30-32: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324440/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as wide as long; punctation sparse and extremely fine, barely noticeable in the pronounced microreticulation. Eyes small, approximately half as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna: antennomere IV weakly transverse; V-X gradually increasing in width and increasingly transverse; X nearly twice as wide as long; XI barely as long as the combined length of IX and X.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FEB5FE73FDAE" blockId="12.[178,1085,373,512]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="1347A39AFFB5F9789304FEB6FEFCFE25" box="[292,366,373,395]" captionStart="Figs 28-37" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1446,1466]" captionTargetBox="[188,1082,208,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[178,1085,208,1418]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 28-37: Bellatheta diacangica nov.sp. (28-32), Tropimenelytron sinuosum nov.sp. (33-35), and Oroekklina excaecata (ASSING) (36-37): (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30-31) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (32) spermatheca; (33) male tergites VI-VII; (34) female tergite VIII; (35) female sternite VIII; (36) male tergite VIII; (37) male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 28: 1.0 mm; 29, 33: 0.5 mm; 34-37: 0.2 mm; 30-32: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324440/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) 1.15-1.25 times as wide as long and 1.05-1.10 times as wide as head; posterior angles weakly marked; in posterior half with more of less pronounced shallow median impression; punctation moderately dense and extremely fine, barely noticeable in the pronounced microreticulation; pubescence of midline directed anteriad in anterior 4/5 and posteriad in posterior 1/5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FDCCFE17FDCE" blockId="12.[178,1086,527,608]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="1347A39AFFB5F9789323FDCCFEC3FD8B" box="[259,337,527,549]" captionStart="Figs 28-37" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1446,1466]" captionTargetBox="[188,1082,208,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[178,1085,208,1418]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 28-37: Bellatheta diacangica nov.sp. (28-32), Tropimenelytron sinuosum nov.sp. (33-35), and Oroekklina excaecata (ASSING) (36-37): (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30-31) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (32) spermatheca; (33) male tergites VI-VII; (34) female tergite VIII; (35) female sternite VIII; (36) male tergite VIII; (37) male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 28: 1.0 mm; 29, 33: 0.5 mm; 34-37: 0.2 mm; 30-32: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324440/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) short, approximately 0.7 times as long as pronotum; humeral angles weakly pronounced; punctation fine and dense; interstices with shallow microsculpture. Hind wings reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FDACFDC0FD54" blockId="12.[178,1085,623,762]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Abdomen approximately 1.1 times as broad as elytra, widest at segments V/VI; tergites III-V with very shallow anterior impression; punctation very fine, moderately sparse on anterior tergites and very sparse on posterior tergites; interstices with shallow, but distinct microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VIII with palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII truncate in the middle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F97892E7FCC9FDCFFC93" blockId="12.[178,1085,778,829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
: sternite VIII distinctly longer than tergite VIII, posterior margin strongly convex; median lobe of aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="1347A39AFFB5F97893C9FCE4FDCBFC93" box="[489,601,807,829]" captionStart="Figs 28-37" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1446,1466]" captionTargetBox="[188,1082,208,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[178,1085,208,1418]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 28-37: Bellatheta diacangica nov.sp. (28-32), Tropimenelytron sinuosum nov.sp. (33-35), and Oroekklina excaecata (ASSING) (36-37): (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30-31) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (32) spermatheca; (33) male tergites VI-VII; (34) female tergite VIII; (35) female sternite VIII; (36) male tergite VIII; (37) male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 28: 1.0 mm; 29, 33: 0.5 mm; 34-37: 0.2 mm; 30-32: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324440/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Figs 30-31</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F97892E7FC8EFD22FCD1" blockId="12.[178,1085,844,895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
: sternite VIII slightly longer than tergite VIII, posterior margin broadly convex, in the middle almost truncate; spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation id="1347A39AFFB5F9789041FCAAFD22FCD1" box="[609,688,873,895]" captionStart="Figs 28-37" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1446,1466]" captionTargetBox="[188,1082,208,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-95@11.[178,1085,208,1418]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 28-37: Bellatheta diacangica nov.sp. (28-32), Tropimenelytron sinuosum nov.sp. (33-35), and Oroekklina excaecata (ASSING) (36-37): (28) habitus; (29) forebody; (30-31) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (32) spermatheca; (33) male tergites VI-VII; (34) female tergite VIII; (35) female sternite VIII; (36) male tergite VIII; (37) male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 28: 1.0 mm; 29, 33: 0.5 mm; 34-37: 0.2 mm; 30-32: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5324440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5324440/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Fig. 32.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FC4CFD23FC6C" blockId="12.[178,1085,911,962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet (adjective) is derived from the name of the mountain range where the 
<typeStatus id="54C701BDFFB5F97893E0FC6EFE7EFC6C" box="[448,492,941,962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FC12FE43FB41" blockId="12.[178,1087,977,1263]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s a n d s y s t e m a t i c s: Basedonitssexualcharacters, particularly to the morphology of the aedeagus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F9789122FC2CFC01FBAA" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[770,915,1006,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacangica">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F9789122FC2CFC01FBAA" box="[770,915,1006,1028]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. diacangica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to some species previously attributed to 
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F9789097FBCFFCA9FB8C" box="[695,827,1036,1058]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Emmelostiba</emphasis>
PACE 1982, which was recently synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F97893F3FBEAFD47FB91" authority="ROUBAL 1928" authorityName="ROUBAL" authorityYear="1928" box="[467,725,1065,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F97893F3FBEAFDA9FB91" box="[467,571,1065,1087]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Bellatheta</emphasis>
ROUBAL 1928
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDC2EEFFB5F97890C5FBEAFCFCFB91" author="VOGEL J" box="[741,878,1065,1087]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref9587" refString="VOGEL J. (2007): Bellatheta fatrica (ROUBAL, 1928) - ein Erstnachweis fur Deutschland mit Bemerkungen zu Synonymien (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Entomologische Blatter 102 (2006) (1 - 3): 101 - 105." type="journal article" year="2007">VOGEL 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The genus, whose monophyly is doubtful and requires revision, currently includes 25 species, four of which have been recorded from mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F36BFF8FFFB5F9789019FBA7FDEBFBD4" box="[569,633,1124,1146]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F97890A9FBA6FC0FFBD4" authority="(PACE 1993)" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[649,925,1124,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F97890A9FBA6FC98FBD4" box="[649,778,1124,1146]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. chinensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDC2EEFFB5F978913EFBA7FC04FBD4" author="PACE R" box="[798,918,1124,1146]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" pagination="69 - 126" refId="ref9246" refString="PACE R. (1993): Aleocharinae della Cina (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 17 (1990): 69 - 126." type="journal article" year="1993">PACE 1993</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F9789191FBA7FB9DFBD4" box="[945,1039,1124,1146]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F9789607FBA6FE3EFB39" authority="(ASSING 2005)" baseAuthorityName="ASSING" baseAuthorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gansuica">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F9789607FBA6FE9FFB39" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. gansuica</emphasis>
(ASSING 2005)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F978939BFB42FD92FB39" box="[443,512,1153,1175]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Gansu</collectingRegion>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F9789034FB41FC87FB39" authority="(PACE 2004)" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[532,789,1153,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellicosa">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F9789034FB41FD1FFB39" box="[532,653,1153,1175]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. bellicosa</emphasis>
(PACE 2004)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F9789103FB42FCE8FB39" box="[803,890,1153,1175]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F978919AFB41FEA7FB1A" authority="(PACE 2004)" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F978919AFB41FBADFB39" box="[954,1087,1153,1175]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. granulosa</emphasis>
(PACE 2004)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F9789366FB5DFE0FFB1A" box="[326,413,1182,1204]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
). All these species have distinctly longer elytra and larger eyes than 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CC49CFFB5F97892C6FB7FFEE7FB7F" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2011" box="[230,373,1211,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bellatheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacangica">
<emphasis id="B908630DFFB5F97892C6FB7FFEE7FB7F" box="[230,373,1211,1233]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">B. diacangica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition they differ in the sexual characters; for illustrations see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDC2EEFFB5F9789292FB1AFEBEFB41" author="PACE R" box="[178,300,1241,1263]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" pagination="69 - 126" refId="ref9246" refString="PACE R. (1993): Aleocharinae della Cina (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 17 (1990): 69 - 126." type="journal article" year="1993">PACE (1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDC2EEFFB5F9789316FB1AFEEAFB41" author="PACE R" box="[310,376,1241,1263]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" pagination="395 - 463" refId="ref9315" refString="PACE R. (1998 b): Aleocharinae della Cina: Parte II (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 105 (2): 395 - 463." type="journal article" year="1998">1998b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDC2EEFFB5F97893A2FB1AFE54FB41" author="PACE R" box="[386,454,1241,1263]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" pagination="457 - 523" refId="ref9431" refString="PACE R. (2004 b): Hygronomini e Athetini della Cina con note sinonimiche (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 111 (3): 457 - 523." type="journal article" year="2004">2004b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3BF1FFFB5F9789292FB3CFC14FAC2" blockId="12.[178,1085,1278,1388]" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d n a t u r a l h i s t o r y: Thetypelocalityissituatedin the Diacang 
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F9789312FAD8FEF5FA9F" box="[306,359,1307,1329]" country="Myanmar" name="Shan" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Shan</collectingRegion>
, to the west of Dali, 
<collectingRegion id="49B871FDFFB5F978901BFADFFD7CFA9F" box="[571,750,1307,1329]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="12" pageNumber="303">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were sifted from litter, moss, and flood debris at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4C8412FAFFB5F97890BCFAFAFD7CFAE0" box="[668,750,1337,1359]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="12" pageNumber="303" unit="m" value="2960.0">2960 m</quantity>
. The adaptive reductions of the eyes and the wings suggest that the species has a restricted distribution.
</paragraph>
